neuragenix.dao
Class Query

java.lang.Object
  neuragenix.dao.Query
public class Query
extends java.lang.Object

This object is the parent class for the DALInsertQuery, DALUpdateQuery and DALSelectQuery. It sets the domains, fields and where causes for it's children objects.

Enables the where fields to be set for the children query objects

Parameters:
strWhereConnector - Requires a valid where connector to be supplied according to the schema
strAFieldName - Requires a valid field name to be set according to the schema
strOperator - Requires a valid operator to be set according to the schema.
strAValue - Requires a field value for the field set. It must be the same type as the field
Throws:
neuragenix.dao.exception.DAOQueryInvalidField - Thrown if a field is supplied that is not in the dbschema.
neuragenix.dao.exception.DAOQueryInvalidFieldValue - Thorwn if the wrong type of fielad value is supplied for a field. E.g., A string is supplied for a integer field
neuragenix.dao.exception.DAOQueryInvalidWhereOperator - Thrown if an operater is supplied that is not in the dbschema
neuragenix.dao.exception.DAOQueryInvalidWhereConnector - Thrown if a connector is supplied that is not defined in the dbschema
java.lang.Exception - Thrown if an unknown error occurs
